&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5285&quot; title=&quot;EOFException during TTF parsing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5285&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5285&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: skip tables that will bring an EOF&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17448735" author="tilman" created="Wed, 24 Nov 2021 17:13:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wanted to close the issue, then had a closer look at your file, the vmtx table is missing 2 bytes, skipping it allows to open the font. Maybe you won&apos;t need that table.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Snapshot is here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfbox-app/2.0.25-SNAPSHOT/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfbox-app/2.0.25-SNAPSHOT/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17448987" author="levrik" created="Thu, 25 Nov 2021 07:41:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; Thanks a lot for implementing this workaround. I&apos;ll give the snapshot a try.&lt;br/&gt;
Are there any plans on releasing a new stable 2.0.x version or will this fix stay on the snapshot forever? I saw that there are a lot of commits on the 2.0 branch since the 2.0.24 release but it seems like PDFBox 3.0 is the main priority.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17449297" author="tilman" created="Thu, 25 Nov 2021 19:00:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, we do both branches, and I expect that the 2.0 branch won&apos;t be abandoned after the 3.0 release, we didn&apos;t abandon the 1.8 branch when 2.0 was released years ago (although it looks abandoned now, must later). I don&apos;t know when 2.0.25 is to be released, I assume this is related to the workload of our release manager.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
